HEADWORD: Heartburn
<hw>Heart"burn`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦ucir⟧rn`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An uneasy, burning sensation in the stomach,
often attended with an inclination to vomit. It is sometimes idiopathic,
but is often a symptom of other complaints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartburned</ent>⟦br⟧
